title: Store owner apologizes for NBA player being refused service - Seattle Post-Intelligencer
text:
In this Oct. 13, 2015, file photo, Milwaukee Bucks' John Henson passes against the Cleveland Cavaliers in the first half of an NBA basketball game in Cleveland. Henson says he was racially profiled at a Wisconsin jewelry store in an incident the shop owner says was a misunderstanding.
 Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
